forms in a talent show; Cricket tries to impress Dr. Eggplant Face.\n| LineColor=df8080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=19\n| EpisodeNumber2=19\n| Title=Cow Duck Avocado<br />Mantis\n| DirectedBy=Cosmo Segurson\n| WrittenBy=Merriwether Williams\n| Aux2=Phil Jacobson and<br />Kahee Lim\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2016|2|19}}\n| ProdCode=119\n| Viewers=0.93<ref>{{Cite web|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 22, 2016|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-19-2016.html|title=Top 50 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: February 19, 2016|publisher=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 23, 2016}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary=Pig becomes the belt of a movie star; Goat finds a movie director; Banana takes role of an avocado; Cricket tries to make a movie on his own. \n| LineColor=df8080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=20\n| EpisodeNumber2=20\n| Title=It's Time to Slumber<br />Party\n| DirectedBy=Kim Roberson\n| WrittenBy=David Sacks and Johnny Ryan\n| Aux2=Sara Jerzykowski and<br />John Trabbic III\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2016|2|26}}\n| ProdCode=120\n| Viewers=0.95<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-26-2016.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILYS-Top 50 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finalese:2.26.2016|work=Showbuzz Daily|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 29, 2016|accessdate=March 2, 2016}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary=Nobody wants to play with Pig; Goat joins the force; Banana does news casting; Cricket picks his nose and tries to stop it.\n| LineColor=df8080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=21\n| EpisodeNumber2=21\n| Title=Secret Origins: Special<br />Edition\n| DirectedBy=Ian Graham\n| WrittenBy=Justin Charlebois, Doug Lieblich,<br />Johnny Ryan, David Sacks,<br />and Merriwether Williams\n| Aux2=Brianne Drouhard and<br />Joe Orrantia\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2016|9|25}}\n| ProdCode=121\n| Viewers={{Small|TB