ana_cricket?lang=en|title=''Pig Goat Banana Cricket'' Season 1|publisher=[[Rogers Cable]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160206134946/http://www.rogersondemand.com/OnDemand/Show/pig_goat_banana_cricket?lang=en|archive-date=February 6, 2016}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pig Goat Banana Cricket Episodes, List Of}}\n[[Category:Lists of American children's animated television series episodes]]\n[[Category:Nickelodeon-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of Nickelodeon television series episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Pig Goat Banana Cricket'' episodes}}\n''[[Pig Goat Banana Cricket]]'' is an [[United States|American]] [[animated television series]] on [[Nickelodeon]]. Created by [[Dave Cooper]] and [[Johnny Ryan]], the series follows the adventures of the eponymous characters Pig ([[Matt Jones (actor)|Matt L. Jones]]), Goat ([[Candi Milo]]), Banana ([[Thomas F. Wilson]]), and Cricket ([[Paul Rugg]]). Most episodes present the escapades of the four characters separately until they meet at the end. The first season premiered on July 16, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Pig-Goat-Banana-Cricket/dp/B011MEY29W|title=''Pig Goat Banana Cricket'' Season 1|publisher=[[Amazon Video]]|accessdate=March 1, 2016}}</ref> \n\nOn June 25, 2015, it was announced that the series had been picked up for a second season of 14 episodes, ahead of the series premiere.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Milo|first=Candi|authorlink=Candi Milo|date=June 24, 2015|url=https://twitter.com/candimilo/status/613760460605620224|title=[Candi Milo announcing the second season]|publisher=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=March 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe second season of the show got moved to sister network [[Nicktoons (United States)|Nicktoons]].<ref>http://tvlistings.zap2it.com/tv/pig-goat-banana-cricket-secret-origins-special-edition/EP022133920021?aid=zap2it</ref> The show ended on August 11, 2018.\n\n== Series overview ==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color1=#df8080\n| link1=List of Pig Goat Banana Cricket episodes#Season 1 (2015\u20132016)\n| episodes1=26\n| start1={{Start date|2015|7|16}}\n| end1={{End date|2016|11|13}}\n\n| color2=#80df80\n| link2=List of Pig Goat Banana Cricket episodes#Season 2 (2016\u20132018)\n| episodes2=14\n| start2= November 20, 2016\n| end2= August 11, 2018\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\nThe episodes below are listed in the order they were originally broadcast.\n\n===Pilot (2012)===\n{{Episode table\n| background=#df80df\n| title=\n| director=\n| writer=\n| airdate=\n| episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| RTitle=''Pig Goat Banana Mantis!''\n| DirectedBy=[[Dave Cooper]] and [[Nick Cross]]\n| WrittenBy=[[Johnny Ryan]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2012|8|13}}\n| ShortSummary=Pig, Goat, Banana, and Mantis live in a semi-isolated cement tree house they inherited from their Old Uncle Robot. They grew up in the tree house, raised by their Uncle, until the trithalium crystals in his cerebrex burned out, causing him to permanently deactivate, leaving them suddenly on their own. Because they all grew up in the same treehouse together, they have developed a really close bond, but they still have very different personalities that often clash in dramatic ways. However, even though they do battle with each other from time to time, they always come together whenever a crisis threatens their home or strange family unit.\n| LineColor=df80df\n}}\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2015\u20132016)===\n{{Episode table\n| background=#df8080\n| season=\n| overall=\n| title=\n| director=\n| writer=\n| aux2=\n| aux2T=Storyboarded by\n| airdate=\n| prodcode=\n| viewers=\n| country=US\n| episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=1\n| EpisodeNumber2=1\n| Title=Pig Goat Banana<br />Cricket High Five!\n| DirectedBy=[[Nick Cross]], [[Ben Jones (Canadian cartoonist)|Ben Jones]],<br />and Gabe Swarr\n| WrittenBy=[[David Sacks]] and [[Johnny Ryan]]\n| Aux2=Nick Cross, Ben<br />Jones, Brian Morante,<br />and Gabe Swarr\n| OriginalAirD